The paper deals with the convergence properties of networks with nonlinear edge functions, which is a topic related to systems and control theory (cs.SY). The use of passivity theory and equivalent circuit models also suggests a connection to mathematical analysis (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the behavior of networks with maximal equilibrium-independent passive (MEIP) dynamics, which is a type of neural network, indicating a possible connection to neural networks (cs.NE). The analysis of steady-state clusters and output agreement is related to the study of dynamical systems (cs.DS). Finally, the use of nonlinear integrators and effective resistance suggests a connection to machine learning and optimization (cs.LG).
